variant_descriptions.PUNPCKLBW: Interleave low-order bytes from xmm1 and xmm2/m128 into xmm1.
variant_descriptions.PUNPCKLWD: Interleave low-order words from xmm1 and xmm2/m128 into xmm1.
variant_descriptions.PUNPCKLDQ: Interleave low-order doublewords from xmm1 and xmm2/m128 into xmm1.
variant_descriptions.PUNPCKLQDQ: Interleave low-order quadword from xmm1 and xmm2/m128 into xmm1 register.
variant_descriptions.VPUNPCKLBW: Interleave low-order bytes from xmm2 and xmm3/m128 into xmm1 register subject to write mask k1.
variant_descriptions.VPUNPCKLWD: Interleave low-order words from xmm2 and xmm3/m128 into xmm1 register subject to write mask k1.
variant_descriptions.VPUNPCKLDQ: Interleave low-order doublewords from xmm2 and xmm3/m128/m32bcst into xmm1 register subject to write mask k1.
variant_descriptions.VPUNPCKLQDQ: Interleave low-order quadword from zmm2 and zmm3/m512/m64bcst into zmm1 register subject to write mask k1.

op.text: Unpacks and interleaves the low-order data elements (bytes, words, doublewords, and quadwords) of the destination operand (first operand) and source operand (second operand) into the destination operand. (Figure 4-22 shows the unpack operation for bytes in 64-bit operands.). The high-order data elements are ignored.
